HEADWORD: Probabiliorist
<hw>Prob`a*bil"i*o*rist</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[From L.
<ets>probabilior</ets>, compar. of <ets>probabilis</ets>
probable.]</ety> <fld>(Casuistry)</fld> <def>One who holds, in
opposition to the probabilists, that a man is bound to do that which is
most probably right.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Probabilism</ent>⟦br⟧
